      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HEREFORAGOODTIME (1) drew wide last start and was never a genuine threat, beaten 16 metres into sixth at this track over 1800m. Starts from a far better position this time and is good enough to take out a race like this. ROLLING REMONA (4) is in good form at present. Finished fourth at her latest appearance over 1800m at this track, beaten 9 metres. Finds a suitable assignment and can discover winning form. STAR MAN (3) was responsible for a better effort last time out when runner-up over 1800m at this track. Should run a big race. TOMMY MACH (7) was out of the money two runs ago then broke and finished ninth last start over 2050m at Port Pirie, coming home 19 metres from the winner. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw. Has the talent to make his presence felt.",
